quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The else Statement[/h1]

Use the [b]else [/b]statement to specify a block of code that will execute if the condition is [b]false[/b].[code format="js" ]if (expression) {
   // executed if condition is true
}
[b]else [/b]{
   // executed if condition is false
}[/code]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to have a valid if...else statement:
[!raw!]
var age = 25;
{0} (age >= 18) {
   alert("Allowed.");
}
{1} {
   alert("Not allowed.");
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The else Statement [/h1]

The example below demonstrates the use of an [b]if...else[/b] statement.[code format="js" codeId="662"]var myNum1 = 7;
var myNum2 = 10;
if (myNum1 > myNum2) {
   alert("This is my first condition");
}
else {
   alert("This is my second condition");
}[/code]
The above example says:
- [b]If [/b][i]myNum1 [/i]is greater than [i]myNum2,[/i] alert "This is my first condition";
- [b]Else[/b], alert "This is my second condition".

The browser will print out the second condition, as 7 is not greater than 10. [img id="2752" width="100%"]
